<refnamediv>
<refname>slidify</refname>
<refpurpose>generate still-frame DVD-Video movies</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>slidify</command>
<arg><replaceable>options ...</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice="req"<replaceable>infile</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice="req"><replaceable>outfile</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>slidify</command>
<arg><replaceable>options ...</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice="req">--magicksrc=<replaceable>magicksrc</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice="req"><replaceable>outfile</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<command>slidify</command> lets you convert a single still-frame image to a movie that
can, for example, be included as part of a DVD-Video slide show, or used as the
background for a DVD-Video menu.
</para>

<para>Command-line options are as follows:</para>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term><literal>--magicksrc=<replaceable>magicksrc</replaceable></literal></term>
<listitem><para>If present, then instead of an input file, the source will be one of the
built-in images provided by ImageMagick.</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><literal>--duration=<replaceable>seconds</replaceable></literal></term>
<listitem><para>Specifies the duration of the output movie to create. Fractions of a second
are allowed. If omitted, defaults to 1.0.</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><literal>--format=pal|ntsc</literal></term>
<listitem><para>Specifies the format of the output movie, either PAL or NTSC. If omitted,
defaults to PAL.</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><literal>--widescreen</literal></term>
<listitem><para>If present, specifies that the aspect ratio of the output movie should be
16:9. If omitted, it will be 4:3.</para></listitem></varlistentry>

</variablelist>

<para>The aspect ratio of the input image will be preserved, with borders added as
necessary to make up the output aspect ratio.

</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>Examples</title>

<para>
<programlisting>slidify --duration=2.5 frame.jpg frame.mpg</programlisting>
</para>
<para>generates a PAL-format movie <literal>frame.mpg</literal> of duration 2.5 seconds
from the image file <literal>frame.jpg</literal>.</para>

<para>
<programlisting>slidify --magicksrc=xc:yellow --format=ntsc yellow.mpg</programlisting>
</para>
<para>generates a 1-second NTSC-format movie consisting of a frame filled with solid yellow.
</para>

<para>
<programlisting>slidify --magicksrc=gradient:'hsb(33%,50%,50%)-hsb(66%,50%,100%)' --widescreen gradient.mpg</programlisting>
</para>
<para>generates a widescreen movie consisting of a linear gradient going from jade green at
the top to blue at the bottom.
</para>

</refsect1>

